WEBVTT

00:08.300 --> 00:12.040
Hi there, welcome to
this video. Today we

00:12.040 --> 00:13.400
are going to learn
what social

00:13.400 --> 00:16.240
engineering is.
Social engineering is

00:16.240 --> 00:18.460
a way attackers trick
people instead of

00:18.460 --> 00:21.080
hacking computers.
The goal of this

00:21.080 --> 00:23.700
video is to explain
social engineering in

00:23.700 --> 00:26.760
a clear and simple
way. We will look at

00:26.760 --> 00:29.120
what it is, how it
works and why

00:29.120 --> 00:31.900
attackers use it.
Understanding this

00:31.900 --> 00:34.360
helps you stay safer
online.

00:37.320 --> 00:39.760
When people hear
about cyberattacks,

00:39.760 --> 00:42.000
they often think
about computers and

00:42.000 --> 00:44.860
code. But many
attacks do not start

00:44.860 --> 00:47.480
with technology. They
start with people and

00:47.480 --> 00:50.320
their behaviour.
People trust others,

00:50.320 --> 00:52.120
want to help and
sometimes feel

00:52.120 --> 00:54.940
pressure to act
quickly. Attackers

00:54.940 --> 00:57.440
know this and use it
to their advantage.

00:57.440 --> 01:00.320
This is why people
are often the target.

01:03.760 --> 01:06.000
Social engineering is
when someone tricks

01:06.000 --> 01:08.160
or manipulates people
into giving away

01:08.160 --> 01:11.660
information, access
or money. It focuses

01:11.660 --> 01:13.960
on human behaviour,
not technical

01:13.960 --> 01:16.720
weaknesses. Instead
of breaking into a

01:16.720 --> 01:18.760
system, attackers
convince someone to

01:18.760 --> 01:21.860
help them. This can
be faster and easier

01:21.860 --> 01:24.020
than hacking. The
victim may not even

01:24.020 --> 01:26.160
realise an attack is
happening.

01:32.040 --> 01:33.940
Attackers may pretend
to be friendly,

01:33.940 --> 01:36.900
helpful or important.
They may create

01:36.900 --> 01:39.060
urgency or fear to
stop people from

01:39.060 --> 01:41.900
thinking carefully.
Sometimes they offer

01:41.900 --> 01:45.000
rewards or prizes.
Attackers usually

01:45.000 --> 01:48.160
have clear goals.
They want information

01:48.160 --> 01:51.560
, access or money.
Social engineering

01:51.560 --> 01:53.500
helps them reach
these goals.

01:55.180 --> 01:57.500
Information can
include passwords,

01:57.500 --> 01:59.260
names, email
addresses or school

01:59.260 --> 02:01.760
accounts. With this
information,

02:01.760 --> 02:04.300
attackers can cause
more problems later.

02:04.300 --> 02:06.120
That is why
information must be

02:06.120 --> 02:09.140
protected. Access
means being able to

02:09.140 --> 02:11.960
log in or use an
account. Once

02:11.960 --> 02:14.140
attackers have access
, they can pretend to

02:14.140 --> 02:16.440
be someone else. This
can lead to serious

02:16.440 --> 02:20.560
problems. Sometimes
attackers want money.

02:20.560 --> 02:23.320
This could be real
money, gift cards or

02:23.320 --> 02:26.580
in-game currency.
Social engineering is

02:26.580 --> 02:28.440
often used to trick
people into sending

02:28.440 --> 02:29.360
it.

02:34.700 --> 02:37.020
Social engineering
can happen online or

02:37.020 --> 02:39.400
offline. It can
happen in messages,

02:39.400 --> 02:42.560
emails, games, phone
calls or face-to-face

02:42.560 --> 02:45.080
. The same tricks can
be used in many

02:45.080 --> 02:48.300
places. Social
engineering works

02:48.300 --> 02:50.880
because people are
human. People trust,

02:50.880 --> 02:53.320
feel emotions and
sometimes act quickly

02:53.320 --> 02:56.440
. Attackers take
advantage of this.

02:57.240 --> 02:59.300
Understanding social
engineering helps you

02:59.300 --> 03:01.700
stop and think. If
something feels

03:01.700 --> 03:05.020
strange or urgent,
slow down. Thinking

03:05.020 --> 03:10.000
first can help you
stay safe. Great work

03:10.000 --> 03:12.080
! In this video you
learned what social

03:12.080 --> 03:14.980
engineering is and
why attackers use it.

03:14.980 --> 03:17.720
Next, watch video
about types of social

03:17.720 --> 03:20.000
engineering to learn
how to recognise them

03:20.000 --> 03:21.900
. Thank you for
watching!

